OL,3,CAmbulance workers threaten strikes
OL,4,Cover 'lack of breaks'
OL,6,F"More of our frontline colleagues are
OL,7,Ffinishing on time and more people are
OL,8,Fgetting their breaks as a result. This
OL,9,Fis about ensuring our people are not
OL,10,Fput at undue risk through working
OL,11,Fexcessive hours or without appropriate
OL,12,Frest breaks, and to improve patient
OL,13,Fsafety.
OL,15,F"We have more than 90 ambulance
OL,16,Fstations across the South West and the
OL,17,Fagreement is that colleagues will take
OL,18,Ftheir breaks at the nearest station
OL,19,Fthat has space.
